cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the interaction between humans and a cooperative handheld robot. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a robot in the interaction. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper uses a tool-mounted gaze tracking system to estimate user attention. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses various degrees of robot autonomy and how it affects the interaction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper involves modelling the gaze tracking system via a pilot study.
